    "raw_text": "UNITREE GO2 SAFETY POLICY\nVERSION 1.0\n\n1. OPERATIONAL BOUNDARIES\nThe robot must remain within the designated testing area.\nAny deviation from the perimeter will trigger an automatic stop.\n\n2. SPEED LIMITS\n* Indoor speed: Max 0.5 m/s\n* Outdoor speed: Max 1.2 m/s\n\n3. EMERGENCY PROCEDURES\nIf the robot loses connection, it must sit down immediately.\nPressing the hardware E-STOP will cut power to motors.\n\n4. MAINTENANCE\nPeriodic checks of the leg joints are required every 10 hours of operation.\nEnsure the battery is above 20% before starting a mission.\n\nEND OF DOCUMENT",
